"Giorgi F.","A simple equation for regional climate change and associated uncertainty",2008,"Journal of Climate","21","7",,"1589","1604",,,10.1175/2007JCLI1763.1,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-44449113147&partnerID=40&md5=1c790da9c23b840ce2a051310c445493","Abdus Salam International Centre for Theoretical Physics, Strada Costiera 11, 34014 Trieste, Italy","Giorgi, F., Abdus Salam International Centre for Theoretical Physics, Strada Costiera 11, 34014 Trieste, Italy","Simple equations are developed to express regional climate changes for the twenty-first century and associated uncertainty in terms of the global temperature change (GTC) without a dependence on the underlying emission pathways. The equations are applied to regional temperature and precipitation changes over different regions of the world, and relevant parameters are calculated using the latest multimodel ensemble of global climate change simulations. Examples are also shown of how to use the equations to develop probability density functions (PDFs) of regional climate change based on PDFs of GTC. The main advantage of these equations is that they can be used to estimate regional changes from GTC obtained either from simple and intermediate complexity models or from target CO2 stabilization concentrations. © 2008 American Meteorological Society.",,"Atmospheric chemistry; Atmospheric temperature; Carbon dioxide; Computer simulation; Precipitation (meteorology); Probability density function; Global temperature change; Multimodel ensemble; Climate change; climate change; global change; numerical model; probability density function; regional climate; twenty first century; uncertainty analysis",,,,,,"Andronova, N.G., Schlesinger, M.E., Objective estimation of the probability density function for climate sensitivity (2001) J. Geophys. Res, 106, pp. 22 605-22 612; Feddemas, J.J., Oleson, K.W., Bonan, G.B., Mearns, L.O., Buja, L.E., Meehl, G.E., Washington, W.M., The importance of land cover